        "2 The GIP is the Generator Interconnection Procedures located in MISO’s Tariff as Attachment X. \n3 The DPP is MISO’s generator interconnection study process, during which MISO performs clustered \ninterconnection studies for specific geographically-organized groups of interconnection requests. MISO conducts \nreliability and deliverability studies that determine whether there is available transmission capacity to \naccommodate the interconnection of a new, proposed generating facility or whether network upgrades are needed.\n[...]\nmilestones under the GIP\n[...]\nthe beginning of DPP Phase I\n[...]\nTariff, Attachment X, Section 7.3.1.4 & Section 7.3.2.4. \n6 See Filing of Revisions to the Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserve Markets Tariff to\n[...]\nQueue Reform became\n[...]\n8 FERC ¶\n[...]\n3 (“201\n[...]\n161 FERC ¶\n[...]\n7 (201\n[...]\n) (“2017 Queue Reform Re\n[...]\nSee, e.g., Midcontinent Ind\n[...]\n. Sys. Operator, Inc., 163 FERC ¶ 61,021 (2018) (order accepting changes to the deadline for Interconnection Customers to revise their Network Resource Interconnection Service election); Midcontinent Indep. Sys. Operator, Inc., 164 FERC ¶ 61,234 (2018) (order accepting changes to the scope of studies performed in DPP Phase I); Letter Order, Revisions to Appendix 1 of Attachment X, FERC Docket Nos. ER19-1103-000, ER19-1103-001 (April 23, 2019) (order accepting changes to improve the processing of hybrid generating facility proposals). 8 Letter Order, Proposed Revisions to MISO Tariff to Close the Post GIA Termination Loophole, Docket No. ER21-525-000 (January 28, 2021). 9 Letter Order, Revisions to Site Control Deadline, Docket No. ER21-1964-000 (June 24, 2021). 10 Letter Order, Surplus Interconnection Service, Docket No. ER21-351-000 (December 22, 2020). 11 Letter Order, Revisions to Attachment X and Attachment X, Appendix 1, Docket No. ER20-1211-000 (April 17, 2020). 12 Midcontinent Indep. Sys. Operator, Inc., 167 FERC ¶ 61,146 (2019)."
      ]
