      "text": "xcelenergy.com | © 2024 Xcel Energy Inc. | Xcel Energy is a registered trademark of Xcel Energy Inc. | 24-04-529\n\nMidcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. (MISO) is an independent system operator (ISO) and Regional Transmission Organization (RTO) that plays a crucial role in the energy market. It provides open-access transmission service and monitors the high-voltage transmission system in the Midwest and southern United States and Manitoba, Canada. The 15 states covered by MISO are Arkansas, Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Kentucky, Louisiana, Michigan, Minnesota, Mississippi, Missouri, Montana, North Dakota, South Dakota, Texas, and Wisconsin, with control centers in Indiana, Minnesota and Arkansas. Beginning with the 2020 – 2021 planning year, each demand resource must validate its performance by meeting the Transmission Provider’s scheduling instructions when called upon during the prior planning year or by conducting a real power test. A demand resource for which a real power test is conducted will receive credit as one (1) of the five (5) deployments or interruptions required for such resource in the planning year in which such a test occurs. A demand resource may provide operational data, or develop an alternative mechanism, subject to the approval of the Transmission Provider, by which the demand reduction capability can be demonstrated without requiring an actual demand reduction if a real power test is precluded or waived due to one of the three conditions as specified below: 1) A real power test is precluded by any applicable regulatory restriction and such a limitation is documented during demand resource registration. 2) Contractual obligations may preclude a test for the 2020-2021 planning year, but not thereafter. Such preclusion must be documented during demand reduction registration or: 3) A Market Participant may waive the obligation to conduct a real power test by notifying the Transmission Provider during demand resource registration and accepting a penalty equal to three (3) times the hourly real-time ex post locational marginal price (LMP) at the load commercial pricing node (CPNode) described in and distributed pursuant to Section 69A.3.9 of the MISO tariff. 1\n\n## MISO TARIFF\n\n1Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. (2024, January). Midcontinent Independent System Operator (MISO). https://www.misoenergy.org/\n\nUPDATED APRIL 2024\n\n",
